   "source": [
    "# Adaptive RK\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's run adaptive RK on  $u'=e^{t-u\\sin u}$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "using FundamentalsNumericalComputation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

       "\u001b[36mODEProblem\u001b[0m with uType \u001b[36mInt64\u001b[0m and tType \u001b[36mFloat64\u001b[0m. In-place: \u001b[36mfalse\u001b[0m\n",

       "u0: 0"

     "metadata": {},

    }
   ],
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "plot(t[1:end-1],diff(t),label=\"\",\n",
    "    xaxis=(\"t\",(0,5)),yaxis=(:log10,\"step size\"),title=\"Adaptive step sizes\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If we had to run with a uniform step size to get this accuracy, it would be"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "4.6096854609878335e-5"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "h_min = minimum(diff(t))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "On the other hand, the average step size that was actually taken was"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.03205128205128205"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "h_avg = sum(diff(t))/(length(t)-1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We took fewer steps by a factor of almost 1000! Even accounting for the extra stage per step and the occasional rejected step, the savings are clear."
   ]
  }
